132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 434
H.P. 288 House of Representatives, February 4, 2025
An Act to Authorize the Maine Governmental Facilities Authority to
Issue Additional Securities for the Replacement of the Legislative
Management System for the Senate and the House of
Representatives
Reference to the Committee on State and Local Government suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Speaker FECTEAU of Biddeford.
Cosponsored by President DAUGHTRY of Cumberland and
Representative: FAULKINGHAM of Winter Harbor, Senator: STEWART of Aroostook.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 4 MRSA §1610-R is enacted to read:
3 §1610-R. Additional securities; legislative branch
4 Notwithstanding any limitation on the amount of securities that may be issued pursuant
5 to section 1606, subsection 2, the authority may issue additional securities in an amount
6 not to exceed $8,000,000 outstanding at any one time for paying the costs associated with
7 planning, purchasing, customizing and implementing an integrated electronic legislative
8 management system to replace the existing system for the Senate and the House of
9 Representatives.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This bill authorizes the Maine Governmental Facilities Authority to issue additional
1122 securities in an amount not to exceed $8,000,000 outstanding at any one time for paying
1133 the costs associated with planning, purchasing, customizing and implementing an
1144 integrated electronic legislative management system to replace the existing system for the
1155 Senate and the House of Representatives.
